Affiliated Managers Names Andrew Dyson to Oversee Distribution

-- B y   C h r i s t o p h e r   C o n d o n
-- 
2011-06-21T12:50:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-21/affiliated-managers-names-andrew-dyson-to-oversee-distribution.html
Affiliated Managers Group Inc. (AMG) , the
company that owns stakes in more than two dozen investment
firms, appointed former  BlackRock Inc. (BLK)  executive Andrew Dyson
head of global distribution.  Dyson, 46, was named executive vice president in charge of
distribution, a newly created position, effective immediately,
the Beverly, Massachusetts-based firm said today in a statement.
Based in  London , Dyson will report to President and Chief
Operating Officer Nathaniel Dalton.  AMGâ€™s affiliated companies managed a combined $340 billion
as of March 31, according to the statement. The firm provides
marketing, distribution and product development support for the
group, which includes Tweedy Browne Co. and Third Avenue
Management LLC, both based in New York.  Dyson left BlackRock, where he was head of global
institutional clients, in December. Before joining BlackRock in
2006 he was with Merrill Lynch Investment Managers.  To contact the reporter on this story:
